Introduction

Base URL: http://localhost

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

Handle an incoming registration request.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"khwibqk\",
    \"email\": \"barbara71@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"soluta\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "khwibqk",
    "email": "barbara71@example.com",
    "password": "soluta"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: khwibqk

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: barbara71@example.com

password   string   

Example: soluta

Handle an incoming authentication request.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"jjaskolski@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"%9JS9XN18]@\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "jjaskolski@example.net",
    "password": "%9JS9XN18]@"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/login

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Example: jjaskolski@example.net

password   string   

Example: %9JS9XN18]@

Handle an incoming new password request.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/reset-password" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"token\": \"voluptate\",
    \"email\": \"anastasia.kuhn@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"nobis\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/reset-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "token": "voluptate",
    "email": "anastasia.kuhn@example.net",
    "password": "nobis"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Mark the authenticated user's email address as verified.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/v1/verify-email/est/molestiae" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/verify-email/est/molestiae"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (401):

Show headers 
cache-control: no-cache, private
content-type: application/json
vary: Origin
 

{
    "message": "Unauthenticated."
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

GET api/v1/verify-email/{id}/{hash}

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the verify email. Example: est

hash   string   

Example: molestiae

POST api/v1/users/assign-role/{user_id}

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/users/assign-role/1" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"roles\": [
        14
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/users/assign-role/1"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {

    --get "http://localhost/api/v1/banks" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/banks"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/banks" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \

}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/banks"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "aaqpyddncrmwulnweasayyff",
    "swift": "bfmfgqxstoytyjoiprrwalv"
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Content-Type

Accept

Body Parameters

employee_id   string   

Example: exercitationem

loan_type_id   string   

Example: voluptatem

amount   number   

Must be at least 0. Example: 21

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: oaqqiundleva

start_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Example: 2024-03-20T06:33:58

expected_end_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Example: 2024-03-20T06:33:58

duration_months   integer   

Must be at least 0. Example: 29

description   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: Ut iste doloribus sed.

status   integer  optional  

Example: 1

Must be one of:
  • 0
  • 1
termination_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. This field is required when status is 1. Example: 2024-03-20T06:33:58
